@thinkofwhy The chest compressions are meant to keep the heart pumping 
blood to the rest of the body (especially the brain!) to limit permanent 
tissue damage....@beyondthisall has a great answer!

@jistrjistr checking heartbeat was once a part of CPR but it was removed 
because people could not find it well enough and they wasted time they 
could have been using for compressions finding a pulse.
